  "text": "Notably, prospective studies show a plateau in mobility recovery within 3 months after stroke in 95% of hemiparetic patients receiving conventional rehabilitation care. [CITATION_1] Our findings in this randomized study show that treadmill training improves both fitness and mobility function long after conventional rehabilitation care has ended, and that the duration of exercise therapy to optimize these outcomes is at least 6 months. These results support a rationale for long-term exercise after stroke, consistent with public health recommendations in the United States for sustained regular exercise to improve fitness and cardiovascular health for all persons.",
